Title this mconf "Tilck Configuration" instead of "BusyBox ...".

host_menuconfig is Tilck's own configurator: run_config drives it
over a generated Kconfig (gen_kconfig.py) whose first line is
`mainmenu "Tilck Configuration"`. Busybox 1.36.1's kconfig, though,
ignores the `mainmenu` directive: conf_parse() unconditionally sets
the root-menu prompt to "Busybox Configuration", and mconf builds
its lxdialog backtitle separately from a hardcoded "BusyBox
<KERNELVERSION> Configuration". Both end up reading "Busybox" no
matter what the Kconfig says.

Fix it in mconf (the hand-written UI driver) rather than the
generated parser: force the root-menu prompt to "Tilck
Configuration" after parsing, then derive the backtitle from that
same prompt. The menu title and the top-of-screen backtitle then
both read "Tilck Configuration". The dead KERNELVERSION lookup that
fed the old backtitle is dropped, with main()'s now-unused `sym`.

Scope: busybox configures itself from a separate, unpatched
extraction of these same kconfig sources, so its own "Busybox
Configuration" UI is unaffected.

--- a/scripts/kconfig/mconf.c
+++ b/scripts/kconfig/mconf.c
@@ -1058,7 +1058,6 @@
 
 int main(int ac, char **av)
 {
-	struct symbol *sym;
 	char *mode;
 	int stat;
 
@@ -1079,10 +1078,18 @@
 	 */
 	sym_change_count = 0;
 
-	sym = sym_lookup("KERNELVERSION", 0);
-	sym_calc_value(sym);
-	sprintf(menu_backtitle, _("BusyBox %s Configuration"),
-		sym_get_string_value(sym));
+	/*
+	 * Tilck patch: busybox's kconfig ignores the `mainmenu`
+	 * directive and hardcodes the root-menu prompt to "Busybox
+	 * Configuration" in conf_parse(). This mconf runs only as
+	 * Tilck's configurator (over run_config's generated Kconfig),
+	 * so force that prompt to Tilck's, then mirror it into the
+	 * lxdialog backtitle (which upstream sets separately to
+	 * "BusyBox <KERNELVERSION> Configuration") so the two agree.
+	 */
+	rootmenu.prompt->text = "Tilck Configuration";
+	snprintf(menu_backtitle, sizeof(menu_backtitle), "%s",
+		menu_get_prompt(&rootmenu));
 
 	mode = getenv("MENUCONFIG_MODE");
 	if (mode) {
